      'tab_name': 'Privacy Policy',
      'tab_content': '<p class="header">MapeaTuDesastre.org Privacy Policy</p><p>Welcome to MapeaTuDesastre.org, a website that collects and shares information about disasters and risks from residents, helping to reduce risk during disaster events. MapeaTuDesastre.org is a project of Yayasan Peta Bencana (YPB) and is operated in collaboration with the Acceleration Laboratory of the United Nations Development Program (UNDP) of Panama.</p><p>Web Server Logs</h2><p>When you visit the Site, including to submit Disaster or Hazard Reports, our web server may record the following information in its server log:</p><ul><li>Your IP address</li><li>The URLs you have requested to access</li><li>The dates and methods of the requests</li><li>The status code of your requests</li><li>URLs of pages that referred you to the site</li><li>Number of bytes transferred</li><li>Your web browser and operating system platform</li><li>Your location (if you provide it)</li><li>Your preferred language (based on browser preferences)</li><li>Your social messaging account: Username or user ID number</li></ul><p>We use server log information to help diagnose problems with our server and administer our website by identifying which parts of the Site are used most frequently. We also use this information to adapt the content of the Site to the users needs and generate aggregated statistical Reports. Web server logs are retained temporarily, during which time their content can be accessed by site administrators and are then completely deleted from our systems. Unless required by legal process, we do not link IP addresses to any personally identifiable information. This means that user sessions will be tracked by IP address, but the users identity will remain anonymous.We do not typically disclose Site usage through individual IP addresses to third parties, but we may do so in very limited circumstances to comply with the law or legal process or when we work with consultants who help us fix or improve the Site or monitor and improve security.</p><p>User-Generated Content</h2><p>User-generated content is collected through Disaster or Risk Reports reports. You can request a disaster or risk report report through the MapeaTuDesastreBot social messaging service. You do not need to register to use disaster reporting, although the information you provide, including your social media username or identification number, is used to provide this service and contact you to confirm receipt of your report card. User-generated content will be available for viewing by all visitors to the Site and will identify you as the author by your social messaging account username.</p><p>All user-generated content that you post on the Site is publicly available to anyone who visits the Site, so please do not post any information that you do not want the general public to know. More information about the information collected through rating reports can be found in our User Agreement.</p><p>Research Access to Data</h2><p>In addition to providing disaster and risk information to residents, MapeaTuDesastre.org facilitates academic research on risk reduction. Any content you post on the Site may be used for academic research.</p><p>Programming Analysis</h2><p>To refine the resources offered through the Site and optimize MapeaTuDesastre.orgs programming, MapeaTuDesastre.org may choose to perform internal analysis of content submitted by users. Any such internal analysis will be performed on an anonymous set of user-generated content.</p><p>Google Analytics</h2><p>We use Google Analytics software to analyze the use of the Site. Google Analytics collects anonymous information from users to help us track Site usage and referrals from other websites. This data is primarily used to optimize the website experience for our visitors, but we may also use the data to assist us in marketing the Site.</p><p>The information collected and processed by Google Analytics includes the users IP address, network location, and geographic location. Google Analytics acquires all its information directly from the user, by installing a cookie (see below) on JavaScript-enabled computers. The Site does not share any information it collects with Google, and Google does not collect any personally identifiable information.</p><p>Cookies</h2><p>Cookies are unique pieces of computer data that many major websites will transfer to your computer the first time you visit them. Cookies are stored on your hard drive and may be accessed later by the website to track previous usage. As noted above, Google Analytics will place a cookie on the hard drives of visitors to the Site.</p><p>Disclosure to Third Parties</h2><p>We will not sell, loan, or disclose any personally identifiable information we collect to third parties, except as discussed in this Policy or as required by law or legal process. We may disclose information to employees, consultants, and agents of Yayasan Peta Bencana or UNDP Panama who have a legitimate need to know information in order to repair or improve the Site and monitor and improve the security of our network. We may also disclose this information when special circumstances require it, such as when disclosure is required by law or legal process or when disclosure is, in our judgment, necessary to protect our legal rights, including intellectual property rights.</p><p>Other Websites</h2><p>This Site may contain links to other web resources, including websites of organizations other than Yayasan Peta Bencana or UNDP. The websites to which the Site links may also place cookies on your computer, record your access to their web pages, or collect user identification information directly from you once you access those sites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of other sites to which the Site links. The privacy policies of those sites, if any, will govern your use of the sites.</p><p>Data Security</h2><p>We have physical, electronic, and managerial procedures in place to protect the information we collect online. However, no matter how effective these measures are, no security system is impenetrable. We cannot completely guarantee the security of our database, nor can we guarantee that information you provide will not be intercepted while being transmitted to us over the Internet.</p><p>Notification of Changes to the Privacy Policy</h2><p>We will review our security measures and Privacy Policy periodically. We may change our Privacy Policy from time to time based on those revisions or because we add or change services or features. If we change our Privacy Policy, we will post it on the Site. We encourage you to review our Privacy Policy periodically.</p><p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, the practices of this Site, or your dealings with this Site, you may contact <a href="mailto:privacy@MapeaYourDesastre.org">privacy@MapeaYourDesastre.org</a> or Yayasan Peta Bencana, Jl. Sumbing No.17, Guntur, Jakarta Selatan 12980, Indonesia.</p>'
